properties.headline: High Surf Advisory issued February 12 at 3:41PM HST until February 14 at 6:00AM HST by NWS Honolulu HI
properties.description:
...HIGH SURF ADVISORY FOR EAST FACING SHORES...

.Increasing trades and a brief period of short to moderate period
easterly wind waves will result in surf above 8 feet along exposed
east facing shores through Thursday. Surf could drop below advisory
level Thursday night into Friday, but will remain elevated through
the weekend.

* WHAT...Surf of 7 to 10 feet.

* WHERE...East facing shores of Kauai, Oahu, Molokai, Maui, and
Big Island.

* WHEN...Until 6 AM HST Friday.

* IMPACTS...Moderate. Expect strong breaking waves, shore break,
and strong longshore and rip currents making swimming difficult
and dangerous.
properties.instruction:
Beachgoers, swimmers, and surfers should heed all advice given by
ocean safety officials and exercise caution.

Boaters should expect recreational surfers and body boarders
utilizing harbor channels to access surfing areas.

NWSheadline: HIGH SURF ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM HST FRIDAY
